Mark order functionalities such as tag identification are not fully
implemented.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update add item in developers guide

commitResults.messageBody:
`marko` functionality allows marking an order as paid and/or delivered
with the -p and -d flag respectively.

In order to support flagging in user input, I have added a new
FlagTokenizer class. Both Flag and Prefix extends ArgumentToken. This is
to allow flexibility in the type of argument tokens that can be stored
in ArgumentMultimap.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add test cases for mark order
commitResults.messageBody:
Fixed bug of flags containing valid flags as being identified as valid
flags.

Added test cases for the following classes:
- MarkOrderCommandParser
- MarkOrderCommand
- FlagTokenizer

This commit adds the functionality of validation sufficient stock before
a user is allowed to mark an order as delivered.

Furthermore, upon marking an order as delivered, the quantity of stock
for delivered items will be decremented correspondingly in the inventory
  list.
